    <note>Li(2) Changyan [7037] He served in the administration of the kings of Wuyue and then became prefect of Hangzhou under Song. Changling's [974] younger brother, Hong's [1037] uncle cousin, Yuqing's [1123] uncle, Zheng(1) Jian's [411]  father-in-law, maternal grandfather of the wives of Lu(9) Gongru [1315] and Wang(2) Gui [1845]. Same generational name as Changfu [972] According to Zeng Gong, in his funerary inscription for Changyan's daughter, who was the wife of Luo(2) Yujing [20040] (q.v.), Changyan often married his daughters to poor scholars (hanshi), who later became famous, e.g. Fan(2) Zhongyan [8043], Zheng(1) Jian [411] and Luo(2) Yujing [who was not very famous]. Luo(2) Yujing's wife was the younger sister of Zeng(1) Gong's [7364] wife's father, Li(2) Yuqing(2) [3553], who was the son of Changyan. Wang Gui, WJ, 51.9b. CBD, 2, 995.</note>
